Unified Hamiltonian Simulation of the Polaron-Molecule Transition on a NISQ Processor
This repository contains the datasets and experimental results associated with the research on simulating quantum phase transitions between polaron and molecule states using Noisy Intermediate-Scale Quantum (NISQ) processors.

Project Overview
The core of this work involves the implementation of a unified Hamiltonian to observe the transition from a polaron to a molecular bound state. Detecting these transitions on current quantum hardware marks a significant step forward in many-body physics and condensed matter simulations.

The demostrations were conducted using the Q-Blue & Q-Red quantum cluster, located in Barcelona, as part of the infrastructure for quantum computing research.

Repository Content
The repository includes the following .csv data files:

matrix spectral data.csv: Spectral data obtained from the Hamiltonian matrix analysis. (Qblue cluster)

qblue results data.csv: Raw and processed results specifically obtained from the Q-Blue quantum cluster in Barcelona. (Qblue cluster)

ramsey signal data.csv: Ramsey spectroscopy signals used to characterize transition frequencies and coherence times on the chip. (Qblue cluster)

validation data.csv: Control datasets used to validate quantum hardware results against theoretical models and classical simulations. (Qblue cluster)

spectrum_N*.csv: Spectral data obtanied to see the scalability. (Qred cluster) (This data have the data treatment done, ZNE, RME...)

dynamics_N*.csv: Dynamic data obtained to see the scalability. (Qred cluster) (This data have the data treatment done, ZNE, RME...)

raw_shots_unmitigated_N10.csv: Is an example of how we obtain the data, this data doesn´t have any data treatment

How to Cite:
If you use this data or the methods described in your research, please cite the original paper:

Catalá Calatayud, H., Valero, E., & Rodrigo, G. (2026). Quantum Simulation of the Polaron-Molecule Transition on a NISQ Device. arXiv preprint 	arXiv:2601.18839
